Phylogenetic analyses were performed using Maximum Likelihood methodologies (RaxML 7.2 . 8 Stamakakis 2006 ) as implemented in the CIPRES web portal V 3.1 (www.phylo.org/portal 2 ). Analyses were run using the recommended default settings, the GTRGAMMA model, and ceasing bootstrapping when MRE-bootstrapping criteria had been reached (in this case after 300 replicates). As analyses included dense intraspecific sampling and many relatively shallow divergences we did not partition the data in order to avoid over-parameterisation. Mean and average uncorrected genetic distances between species were calculated using PAUP *V.b 8 (
Swofford 2000
).

